    "reasoning": "The process involves three main steps: deriving the interface, implementing the sequential logic requirement in the testbench, and updating the final reporting.\n\n**1. Interface Derivation (Following Golden Testbench):**\nThe `golden_testbench` instantiates `TopModule` as: `TopModule top_module1 ( .clk, .a, .q(q_dut) );`. This means the interface must be: `input clk`, `input a`, `output logic [2:0] q`. All ports are declared as `logic` for modern SystemVerilog practices, matching the usage in the TB.\n\n**2. Testbench Improvement (Queue Implementation for Sequential Logic):**\n*   Since `TopModule` is sequential, I must implement the queue-based mismatch display logic as detailed in the prompt's example.\n*   **MAX_QUEUE_SIZE:** Since `q` is 3 bits, $2^3 = 8$. I set `MAX_QUEUE_SIZE = 8`.\n*   **Queues:** I define queues for inputs (`clk`, `a`), DUT output (`q_dut`), Reference output (`q_ref`), and a 'reset' proxy (though no reset is present, tracking inputs is crucial for context).\n*   **Synchronization:** All queue management and mismatch checking must occur within the `always @(posedge clk, negedge clk)` block, synchronized with the clock.\n*   **Mismatch Logic:** The original verification logic (`tb_match` and `stats1` updates) must be maintained. The new queue logic will run in parallel, and upon the *first* mismatch detected by the queue mechanism, it will display the historical data.\n*   **Error Counting:** The existing `stats1.errors` and `stats1.errors_q` counting logic based on `tb_match` and `q_ref !== (q_ref ^ q_dut ^ q_ref)` must be preserved.\n\n**3. Final Reporting:**\n*   The original `final` block needs to be completely replaced/augmented to adhere to the new requirement:\n    *   If `stats1.errors == 0` (no mismatches found), display: `SIMULATION PASSED`.\n    *   If `stats1.errors > 0` (mismatches found), display: `SIMULATION FAILED - x MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME y`, where $x = stats1.errors$ and $y = stats1.errortime$.\n\n**Advice to Avoid Syntax Errors:**\n*   When using queues in SystemVerilog, ensure correct usage of `push_back()` and `delete(0)`.\n*   When displaying multi-bit signals, use `%h` for hexadecimal and `%b` for binary, as required, especially for the queued data.\n*   The queue checking must happen inside the clocked `always` block to ensure synchronized comparison.\n*   The queue size must be set correctly (`MAX_QUEUE_SIZE = 8`) and used consistently for queue operations.\n\n**Crucial Modification:** I will modify the `always @(posedge clk, negedge clk)` block to handle both the state tracking (queueing) and the original statistical counting, ensuring the queue reporting triggers only upon the very first mismatch.",
    "interface": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input a,\n    output logic [2:0] q\n);\nendmodule",
    "testbench": "`timescale 1 ps/1 ps\n`define OK 12\n`define INCORRECT 13\n\n// --- Stimulus Generator (Kept as is) ---\nmodule stimulus_gen (\n\tinput clk,\n\toutput logic a,\n\toutput reg[511:0] wavedrom_title,\n\toutput reg wavedrom_enable\n);\n\n\ttask wavedrom_start(input[511:0] title = \"\");\n\tendtask\n\t\ntask wavedrom_stop;\n\t\th#1;\n\tendtask\n\n\tinitial begin\n\t\ta <= 1;\n\t\t@(negedge clk) {a} <= 1;\n\t\t@(negedge clk) wavedrom_start(\"Unknown circuit\");\n\t\t\trepeat(2) @(posedge clk);\n\t\t@(posedge clk) {a} <= 0;\n\t\t\trepeat(11) @(posedge clk);\n\t\t@(negedge clk) a <= 1;\n\t\t\trepeat(5) @(posedge clk, negedge clk);\n\t\ta <= 0;\n\t\trepeat(4) @(posedge clk);\n\t\twavedrom_stop();\n\n\t\trepeat(200) @(posedge clk, negedge clk)\n\t\ta <= &((5)'($urandom));\n\t$finish;\n\tend\n\tendmodule\n\n// --- Testbench Module (Improved) ---\nmodule tb();\n\n\ttypedef struct packed {\n\t\tint errors;\n\t\tint errortime;\n\t\tint errors_q;\n\t\tint errortime_q;\n\t\tint clocks;\n\t} stats;\n\t\n\tstats stats1;\n\t\n\t\n\twire[511:0] wavedrom_title;\n\twire wavedrom_enable;\n\tint wavedrom_hide_after_time;\n\t\n\treg clk=0;\n\tinitial forever\n\t\th#5 clk = ~clk;\n\n\tlogic a;\n\tlogic [2:0] q_ref; // Reference output\n\tlogic [2:0] q_dut; // DUT output\n\n\t// --- Queue Management Declarations ---\n\t// q is 3 bits. MAX_QUEUE_SIZE >= 2^3 = 8. Set to 8.\n\tlocalparam MAX_QUEUE_SIZE = 8;\n\t\n\t// Signals to store in queues\n\treg [2:0] input_a_q [$];\n\treg [2:0] output_q_dut_q [$];\n\treg [2:0] golden_q_ref_q [$];\n\treg reset_q [$]; // Tracking reset/strobe proxy if needed, using 1-bit\n\n\t// Mismatch tracking for queue display\n\treg mismatch_detected_q = 0;\n\t\n\tinitial begin \n\t\t$dumpfile(\"wave.vcd\");\n\t\t$dumpvars(1, stimulus_gen::stim1.clk, tb_mismatch, clk, a, q_ref, q_dut);\n\tend\n\n\t// Verification Signals\n\twire tb_match;\n\twire tb_mismatch = ~tb_match;\n\t\n\t// Instantiate DUT and stimulus\n\tstimulus_gen stim1 (\n\t\t.clk,\n\t\t.a,\n\t\t.wavedrom_title,\n\t\t.wavedrom_enable \n\t);\n\tRefModule good1 (\n\t\t.clk,\n\t\t.a,\n\t\t.q(q_ref) );\n\tTopModule top_module1 (\n\t\t.clk,\n\t\t.a,\n\t\t.q(q_dut) );\n\n\t// Task to wait for time step end (Kept as is)\n\tbit strobe = 0;\n\ttask wait_for_end_of_timestep;\n\t\trepeat(5) begin\n\t\tstrobe <= !strobe;  // Try to delay until the very end of the time step.\n\t\t@(strobe);\n\t\tend\ttask\n\n\t// Verification assignment (Kept as is)\n\tassign tb_match = ( { q_ref } === ( { q_ref } ^ { q_dut } ^ { q_ref } ) );\n\n\t// Clocked Process for Stats, Queueing, and Mismatch Reporting\n\talways @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\n\t\t// --- 1. Statistics Update (Original Logic) ---\n\t\tstats1.clocks++;\n\t\tif (!tb_match) begin\n\t\t\tif (stats1.errors == 0) stats1.errortime = $time;\n\t\t\tstats1.errors++;\n\t\t\tend\n\t\t// Original q_ref vs q_dut check (kept for compatibility)\n\t\tif (q_ref !== ( q_ref ^ q_dut ^ q_ref ))\n\t\tbegin \n\t\t\tif (stats1.errors_q == 0) stats1.errortime_q = $time;\n\t\t\tsstats1.errors_q = stats1.errors_q+1'b1; \n\t\tend\n\t\t\n\t\t// --- 2. Queue Management (New Requirement) ---\n\t\t\n\t\t// Dequeue if full\n\t\tif (input_a_q.size() >= MAX_QUEUE_SIZE - 1) begin\n\t\t\tinput_a_q.delete(0);\n\t\t\toutput_q_dut_q.delete(0);\n\t\t\tgolden_q_ref_q.delete(0);\n\t\t\treset_q.delete(0);\n\t\tend\n\n\t\t// Enqueue current data\n\t\tinput_a_q.push_back(a);\n\t\toutput_q_dut_q.push_back(q_dut);\n\t\tgolden_q_ref_q.push_back(q_ref);\n\t\treset_q.push_back(1'b0); // Assuming no explicit reset signal present\n\n\t\t// Check for first mismatch ONLY if not already detected\n\t\tif (!mismatch_detected_q && (q_dut !== q_ref)) begin\n\t\t\tmismatch_detected_q = 1;\n\t\t\t$display(\"================================================================================================\");\n\t\t\t$display(\"!!! FIRST MISMATCH DETECTED AT TIME %0t !!!\", $time);\n\t\t\t$display(\"Displaying Last %0d Cycles of Simulation (Queue Size: %0d):\n\", MAX_QUEUE_SIZE, input_a_q.size());\n\n\t\t\tfor (int i = 0; i < input_a_q.size(); i++) begin\n\t\t\t\t// Check for mismatch in the historical window\n\t\t\t\tif (output_q_dut_q[i] !== golden_q_ref_q[i]) begin\n\t\t\t\t\ts$display(\"-> Mismatch occurred at Cycle %0d\", i);\n\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\t\t$display(\"Cycle %0d | Input a: %b | Ref q: %h (%b) | Got q: %h (%b)\",\n\t\t\t\ti,\n\t\t\t\tinput_a_q[i],\n\t\t\t\tgolden_q_ref_q[i],\n\t\t\t\tgolden_q_ref_q[i], \n\t\t\t\toutput_q_dut_q[i],\n\t\t\t\toutput_q_dut_q[i]);\n\t\t\tend\n\t\t\t$display(\"================================================================================================\");\n\t\tend\n\tend\n\n\t// Timeout logic (Kept as is)\n\tinitial begin\n\t\t#1000000\n\t\t$display(\"TIMEOUT\");\n\t\t$finish();\n\tend\n\n\t// Final reporting logic (Updated) \n\tfinal begin\n\t\tif (stats1.errors == 0) \n\t\t\t$display(\"SIMULATION PASSED\");\n\t\telse \n\t\t\t$display(\"SIMULATION FAILED - %0d MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME %0d\", stats1.errors, stats1.errortime);\n\tend\n\nendmodule"
}
